<p>Hi,</p>

<p>
  The automated BACS check ran on <strong><%= @run_date %></strong> and found
  <%= @rows.size %> <%= "submission".pluralize(@rows.size) %> that
  <%= @rows.size == 1 ? "has" : "have" %> been <strong>waiting for approval</strong>
  for more than <%= @threshold_days %> days. The automated batch only acts on
  <em>approved</em> expenses, so these need someone to approve (or reject) them on the
  Review page before anything can happen.
</p>

<table border="1" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="4" style="border-collapse: collapse; font-family: sans-serif; margin-bottom: 1em;">
  <thead style="background-color: #f0f0f0;">
    <tr><th>#</th><th>Payee</th><th>Amount</th><th>Waiting</th></tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <% @rows.each do |row| %>
      <tr>
        <td>#<%= row[:auto_number] %></td>
        <td><%= row[:payee_name] %></td>
        <td>&pound;<%= row[:amount] %></td>
        <td><%= row[:age_days] %> <%= "day".pluralize(row[:age_days]) %></td>
      </tr>
    <% end %>
  </tbody>
</table>

<p>Open the Review page to approve or reject <%= @rows.size == 1 ? "it" : "them" %>.</p>

<p>Best,<br>Bedlam Fringe BACS (automated)</p>
